      "role": "user",
      "content": "idk about aesthetics or sunlight... it feels more technical than that. i was looking at some old drawings of the layout near trinity church in nyc and then compared them to the street alignments in central london. the angles are almost identical. like, if you drew a line from the spire of one to the base of the other, it's the exact same degree of tilt. it's too specific to be just \"topography.\" does that happen often with old colonial cities or is that just me seeing things?",
